==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frustum
<hw>Frus"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Frusta</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Frustums</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>fruslum</ets> piece, bit.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>The part of a solid next the
base, formed by cutting off the, top; or the part of any solid, as of a
cone, pyramid, etc., between two planes, which may be either parallel or
inclined to each other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>One of the drums of the shaft of
a column.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frutage</ent>⟦br⟧
